vex border of the falx will be made manifest by the escape
of blood through numerous small veins, when the finger is
carried backwards along the middle line. When the sinus Situais opened, it is seen to be narrow in front, and to become ending.
wider as it proceeds backwards, till it ends in a common
point of union of certain sinuses (torcular Herophili). Its
