Veins opening This sinus receives small veins from the substance and the
into it. exterior of the skull, and larger ones from the hemispheres
of the brain. The cerebral veins open chiefly at the posterior part of the brain, and lie for some distance against the
wall of the sinus before they perforate it ; their course is
likewise directed from behind forwards, so that the motion
Current of the blood in them is directly opposed to the current in the
sinus. This disposition of the veins may be seen on the left
side, where the parts are undisturbed.
