Eye- lashes.
DifferThe eyelashes (cilia ) are two or more rows of long hairs,
which are fixed into the anterior edge of the free border of
the lid ; they are largest in the upper lid, and diminish in
length from the centre towards the sides. The cilia are so
arranged as to be convex towards one another.
