follows : -the second nerve enters the eyeball, the third is
furnished to all the muscles but two, the fourth enters the
superior oblique (one of the two excepted), and the sixth is
spent in the external rectus muscle. The fifth nerve supplies some filaments to the eyeball, but the greater number
of its branches pass through the orbital cavity to the face.
