The OPHTHALMIC or LENTICULAR GANGLION is a small Lenticuroundish body, of the size of a pin's head, and of a reddish lion.
colour. It is placed at the back of the orbit, between the Situaoptic nerve and the external rectus, and commonly on the
outer side ofthe ophthalmic artery. By its posterior part the Connecganglion has branches of communication with other nerves
(its roots), and from the anterior part proceed the ciliary
nerves to the eyeball. In the ganglion are combined sen- Strucsory, motory, and sympathetic filaments.
