3. Thyroid axis.— This is a short thick trunk, that arises from
the front ofthe artery near the anterior scalenus muscle, and soon
divides divides into three branches : one to the thyroid body, and two
to the scapula that run outwards across the neck. On the left
side of the body the thoracic duct lies in front of the thyroid axis.
