The MYLO- HYOID MUSCLE is triangular in shape, with the Mylo- hyoideus base at the jaw and the apex at the hyoid bone, and unites
along the middle line with its fellow of the opposite side. It arises
arises from the ridge ( mylo-hyoid) on the inner surface of jaw ;
the jaw, and is inserted into the body of the hyoid bone, as inserted
well as into a central line between the jaw and that bone. hyoid
