The INTERNAL CAROTID ARTERY supplies the parts within Internal
the head, viz. the brain and the orbit, and takes its name
from its distribution. Springing from the bifurcation of the
common carotid trunk, this artery extends from the upper enters
border of the thyroid cartilage to the base of the skull, then
through the petrous portion of the temporal bone, and
lastly along the base of the skull to the anterior clinoid process, where it ends in branches for the brain. This winding Its
course of the artery may be divided into three parts :
one part in the neck, another inside the skull, and a third
in the temporal bone.
