has three similar cord in the thorax. On this part of the nerve are
three ganglia ; one near the skull, another on the neck of
the first rib, and a third midway between the two ; these are
named respectively superior, middle, and inferior ganglion.
From the ganglia proceed some branches that are connected
with the spinal and most of the cranial nerves, and other
branches that are distributed to viscera.
