œsophagus and thoracic duct ; and the pleura is in contact
with the anterior and outer parts.
The pneumo-gastric nerve is in connection with this part of
the artery, but its position is parallel to the vessel instead of
across it, as on the right side. The internal jugular vein,
jugular in like manner, is parallel to the artery for a short distance,
and superficial to it. Accompanying also the subclavian
artery are the cardiac branches of the sympathetic, which
course along the side of the vessel to the chest.
