Mucous The mucous membrane ofthe pharynx is continuous anbrane of teriorly with the mucous lining of the mouth and nose.
pharynx conti- Covering the soft palate and its numerous small glands
(palatine), the membrane is continued to the tonsils on each
side, and is prolonged by the Eustachian tubes to the tympanum. From the dorsum of the tongue it is continued over
the epiglottis, forming its three small anterior folds, and
then lines the pharynx. In front of each arytenoid cartilage it encloses a mass of muciparous glands (arytenoid),
and then sends a prolongation into the larynx. Inferiorly,
it is continued by the oesophagus to the stomach.
