the stylo-glossus are directed forwards along the border of the
tongue ; and internal to these are the fibres of the palatoglossus and hyo-glossus, which mix with them. In the
middle line, from base to apex, are implanted the vertical
fibres of the genio-hyo-glossus. These muscles have been
