The ARYTÆNOIDEUS is a single muscle in the middle line,
and is placed in the concavity on the posterior aspect of the
arytenoid cartilages, to which it is attached. Two sets of
fibres with different directions are seen in the muscle. The
superficial fibres consist of two oblique fasciculi , which cross
like the parts of the letter X, each passing from the base of
and deep one cartilage to the apex of the other. The deep fibres are
transverse, and are inserted into the outer border and the
posterior surface of the cartilages ; they close the interval
between the cartilages. A few of the oblique fibres of the
muscle are usually continued round the cartilage to join the
thyro-arytenoid muscle, or the fibres in the arytenoepiglottidean fold of mucous membrane.
