Dissection. -Open the tube of the larynx by dividing it along
the posterior part ; and in cutting through the arytenoid muscle expose
let the incision be rather to the right of the middle line, to
avoid the nerves that enter it. On looking into the larynx a
depression (ventricle) is seen on each side ; and if a probe is passed
into this hollow it will be found to enter a small pouch by an
aperture in the anterior part. The dissector is to fill the pouch
on the right side by introducing very small round bits of cotton
wool into it.
