the larynx, furnishes backwards an offset to the mucous membrane of the pharynx, which joins with filaments from the
supplies laryngeal nerve. The nerve then passes beneath the ala of the thy- special roid cartilage, and ends in branches for the different special muscles
except of the larynx, except the crico- thyroideus. Its small muscular
muscles
