Dissec- tion.
An an- terior,
Dissection. - For the examination of the ligaments in the
sterno-clavicular articulation, take the piece of the sternum that
was laid aside for that purpose. Remove the cellular membrane
from the several ligaments ; and should these have become dry,
they ought first to be moistened for a short time.
The anterior ligament is attached by a narrow point to
