The PIA MATER, or the vascular covering of the brain, Pia maclosely invests the different parts of the cranial mass, and
dips into the fissures, as well as into the hollows between the
convolutions and the lamina. Besides covering the exterior sends pieces of the brain, it sends processes into the interior to supply into the
vessels to the walls of the enclosed spaces : thus, one penetrates into the cerebrum below the corpus callosum, and is
named velum interpositum ; and two vascular fringes project into the fourth ventricle, and are known as the choroid
plexuses of that ventricle.
