This membrane is a net-work of vessels, and is conof blood- structed chiefly out of the minute ramifications of the
arteries before they enter the substance of the brain ; the
intervals between the vessels being closed by cellular tissue,
so as to form a continuous membrane. From the under
surface of the pia mater proceed numerous fine vessels for
the nutrition of the brain.
