of the pneumo-gastric next below ; both these form projections in the
floor of the fourth ventricle, near the lower part of the calamus scriptorius. The nucleus of the spinal accessory nerve is contained in the
medulla, lower down than the preceding.
nerve. The NINTH or HYPO-GLOSSAL NERVE of Willis (twelfth Ninth
