(foramen cæcum), the posterior is prolonged behind the pons,
and forms the groove in the floor of the fourth ventricle.
Each half of the medulla is marked by the following projec- Compotions, which are situate from before backwards in the order each
now mentioned, viz. the anterior pyramid, the olivary body,
the restiform body, and, lastly, the posterior pyramid.
