tia
The corpora albicantia (corp. mamillaria) are two small,
white bodies, about the size of peas, which are formed in
greater part by the crus of the fornix (to be afterwards seen).
If one, say the left, is cut across, it will be found to contain
grey matter ; and grey matter also surrounds it.
