This body is situate in the sella Turcica, or the hollow ofthe
body of the sphenoid bone, and consists of two lobes, anterior and posterior. The anterior is the largest, and is concave behind, where it receives the posterior lobe. In the
adult this mass is firm and solid, but in the foetus it is hollow,
and opens into the third ventricle through the infundibulum.
