cerebri, and ends at the posterior part of the same spot. Whilst
lying on the inner surface of the hemisphere, it is joined by the
convolutions of that part. Beneath this convolution is a band of its fillet
fibres (covered band of Reil, fillet of the corpus callosum), which is connected in front and behind with the anterior perforated spot,
and gives offsets to other secondary convolutions in the longitudinal fissure.
