Structure of the convolutions. —From the section now made into
has base the brain, it appears that each convolution is continuous with the
summit ; interior of the brain on the one side (base), and that it is free on
the surface of the brain on the other side, where it presents a
summit and lateral parts. Externally it consists of a layer of grey
cerebral substance (cortical layer), which is continuous over the
surface of the hemisphere ; and internally it is composed of a white
cerebral substance (medullary part), which is a prolongation from
the fibres of the interior.
