The peduncular fibres, in ascending to the cerebrum, have the Fibres of
following disposition in the striate body and the optic thalamus. peduncle
Those that form the free or fasciculated part of the peduncle pass andopthrough the middle of the striate body ; whilst those on the opposite tic thaaspect of the peduncle, which form its tegmentum, are transmitted
chiefly through the under part of the optic thalamus. In these
