and the thalamus, the fibres radiate into the anterior, middle, and sphere
posterior parts of the cerebral hemisphere, forming the corona they exradiata. In the hemisphere the fibres are continued to the convo- convolu
lutions, but before reaching the circumference of the brain they
decussate with the converging fibres of the corpus callosum.
Their expansion in the hemisphere resembles a fan bent down in
front and behind, forming thus a layer which is concave on the
under side.
