Structure of the optic thalamus. -On making sections of the
optic thalamus on the side on which it is entire (the left) , this body
will be found to consist of layers of grey and white substance at
the upper and inner parts ; but only of the medullary fibres (tegmentum) of the peduncle of the cerebrum at the lower and outer
parts.
