INTERIOR OF THE CEREBELLUM.-In the cerebellum there Cereis not any cavity or ventricle enclosed, for the space of the solid infourth ventricle is between the cerebellum and the medulla
oblongata. In the interior there is a large white centre,
like that of the cerebrum, which furnishes offsets to the
laminæ, and to other parts of the encephalon.
