Dissection. -Turn upwards the superior aspect of the cere- Dissecbellum, and make an incision across the laminæ of the left hemisphere to see their structure. On the right lobe place the scalpel
in the horizontal fissure, and carry it inwards as far as the superior
vermiform process, so as to cut away all the laminar structure, and
expose the medullary substance with the contained corpus den- tatum.
