MEDULLARY CENTRE. -
A large white mass occupies the
centre of the cerebellar hemisphere, and contains in its substance a dentate body. From its surface offsets are furoffsets, nished to the different laminæ, and from the anterior part
proceed three large processes or peduncles-superior, middle,
and inferior.
