The superficial lymphatics of the arm lie for the most part along
lympha- the basilic vein, and open into the glands of the axilla. A few
lymphatics accompany also the cephalic vein, and passing between
the pectoral and deltoid muscles, end as the others in the axillary
glands. A lymphatic gland is commonly found as low as the
elbow, where it lies in front ofthe inner condyle of the humerus.
