Dissection. -For the dissection of the back of the arm turn over
the back the limb, and raise it to a semi-flexed position by means of a block
of moderate thickness, beneath the elbow. Fasten also the scapula
with hooks, in order that the muscular fibres may be rendered
tense. Then the detached skin being thrown aside, make a central incision in the fascia to a little below the elbow, and raise it
with the subfascial cellular membrane from the surface of the
large triceps muscle.
