Dissection. - Cut through the origin of the flexor carpi radialis Dissecand palmaris longus, near the inner condyle of the humerus, and
turn these muscles to one side. Small branches of the ulnar
artery and median nerve will be seen to enter the under surface of the muscles. For the present, the pronator teres may be
left uncut. The remaining muscle of the superficial layer (flexor
sublimis digitorum) is now exposed in the fore- arm.
