to those of the deep flexor ; and the four tendons are nearly
on the same level, instead of being arranged in pairs as in
the fore-arm. Crossing the palm of the hand, the tendons
enter the sheaths of the fingers, and are inserted by two
processes into the margins of the middle phalanx, about the
