CONNECTIONS OF THE LUNG.
The lungs are two in number, and are contained in the Number
cavity of the thorax, one on each side of the spinal column.
In these organs the changes in the air and blood during and use.
respiration take place.
The lung is of a conical form, and is covered by the bag Form.
of the pleura. It presents for examination a base and apex,
two borders, two surfaces, lobes, and fissures, together with
