The root is situate about midway between the base and situaapex, and about a third of the breadth of the inner surface
from the posterior border of the lung. In front of the root, Connec
on both sides, are the phrenic nerve and the anterior pulmonic plexus, but anterior to the right root is the descending
cava. Behind, on both sides, is the posterior pulmonic
plexus ; and on the left side there is, in addition, the descending aorta. Above, on the right side, is the vena azygos,
and on the left side the arch of the aorta. Below each root
is the fold of pleura called ligamentum latum pulmonis.
