Occupying the middle line of the chest, the heart projects
heart to also to the left side ; and it may be said to reach one inch or
one inch and a-half to the right of the centre of the sternum,
and three inches to three inches and a-half to the left of that
line. Its position to the axis of the body is oblique from
right to left, with the left border upwards, and the right
border downwards. The apex is opposite the space between
the cartilages of the fifth and sixth ribs of the left side,
"two inches below the nipple, and one on its sternal side."
