The auricles are two, as before said ( right and left), and are Situaplaced at the base of the heart behind the aorta and the the
pulmonary artery. They receive their appellation from the
resemblance that the tips or appendices projecting forwards
on the sides of the arteries bear to a dog's ears.
auricles are much thinner than the ventricles, and are reci- these
pients of blood from large veins. Of the two, the right is
rather the larger and more anterior ; it is joined by the
upper and the lower cava, and by the veins of the substance
of the heart. The left cavity receives the two pulmonary Left.
