Dissection. Before opening the heart, the vessels for the nutri- Dissect
tion of its substance ( coronary arteries) should be dissected on the
surface, together with the small nerves that accompany them.
The small vessels appear on the sides of the pulmonary artery, and
occupy the grooves on the surface of the heart, where they are
surrounded by fat ; one branches over the right, and the other
over the left side. With the anterior artery is a plexus of nerves,
which is to be followed upwards to the superficial cardiac plexus ;
with the remaining artery is another plexus.
