The valves are formed by fibrous tissue, covered by the struclining membrane of the vessel. The use of these little and use.
valves is obvious, viz. to give free passage to fluid in one
direction, or to close the area of the vessel. Whilst the
blood is entering the artery, the valves are placed against the
wall ; but when the vessel acts on the contained blood, the
valves are thrown towards the centre of the cavity, and prevent the return of the circulating fluid into the ventricle.
