STRUCTURE. The heart is composed of a mass of muscular fibres, and of certain fibrous rings which serve as fixed
fibrous points for their attachment. These structures must be
cular. studied on the heart of the ox or sheep, in which the fibres
have been hardened and separated by boiling.
