Peculiarities. The number of these veins may be altered ; first, by
the union of the veins of the left side into one ; and, secondly, by the
want ofunion on the right side, from which three trunks result, corresponding to three lobes. But other peculiarities may be found as to
number, for six or seven veins have been observed taking both sides
together, and a bronchial vein has been found opening into one of the left veins.
