The TRACHEA, or the air tube, reaches from the larynx to
the lungs, and lies on the front of the spinal column. The
tube begins at the lower part of the larynx, opposite the
fifth cervical vertebra, and ends at the third dorsal vertebra
and in by dividing into two pieces (bronchi), one for each lung.
thorax, Its connections in the neck are described at p. 115., and its
ends in structure at p. 153. The part in the thorax remains to be
