The complexus and biventer cervicis muscles are concealed by the splenius and trapezius ; and the cutaneous
surface of the complexus presents a tendinous cross intersection. Two or three of the cervical nerves perforate the
complexus. Along the inner side is the semispinalis muscle,
with the ligamentum nucha. Beneath the muscle are the
small recti and obliqui muscles, the semispinalis, and the
cervical nerves.
