It gives On each side the dura mater furnishes offsets to the different
spinal spinal nerves issuing by the intervertebral foramina ; and
inferiorly these several offsets form small tubes which enclose
the sacral nerves, and lie for some distance within the spinal
and one canal. In the midst of these tubes, into which the dura
inferior mater is divided below, will be seen a slender impervious
cord, that descends from the lower part of the dura mater
to the end of the spinal canal, and is blended with the periosteum covering the back of the coccyx.
