DIVISIONS OF THE CORD. - Each half of the cord, viz.
divided from the anterior to the posterior median fissure, is divided
into two parts by the lateral slit or fissure. The piece in
front of that line ( posterior roots of the nerves) is called the
antero-lateral column, and the piece behind, the posterior
column.
antero- lateral a. The antero- lateral column includes rather more than
column two-thirds of the surface of the half of the cord, extending
backwards to the posterior roots of the nerves, and gives attachment to the anterior roots. By some anatomists it is
divided into two parts (an anterior and a lateral column)
by a supposed fissure along the attachment of the anterior
roots. *
