aspect of the cord. On the surface of this division, near the
median fissure, is a slight groove or furrow, marking off a
slender piece, the posterior median column, which terminates
superiorly in the posterior pyramid of the medulla oblongata. This separation is best seen in the cervical part of
the cord.
