The EXTERNAL SPHINCTER (sphincter ani externus) is a Exterflat, thin, orbicular muscle, which is pointed in front and sphincbehind, and surrounds the lower part of the rectum. Like rounds
other orbicular muscles, the fibres form elipses around a
central aperture. The muscle arises posteriorly from the tip origin.
of the coccyx by a fibrous band, and from the superficial
fascia in front of that bone. The fibres pass forwards to the
anus, where they separate to encircle that aperture, and
having again united in front of it, are inserted into the Insersuperficial fascia and the central point of the perinæum.
