ARTERIES. -The inferior hæmorrhoidal is the only named
branch of the pudic artery that is now exposed. Some other
small branches of the pudic and sciatic are also seen.
Inferior The inferior hæmorrhoidal artery arises from the trunk of the
rhoidal pudic, internal to the tuberosity of the ischium, and divides into
branches that pass inwards across the ischio- rectal fossa to end in
ends on the skin and the sphincter and levator ani muscles. On the
and in its rectum this artery anastomoses with the middle hæmorrhoidal
artery ofthe internal iliac, and with the artery of the opposite side.
In a well-injected body, some cutaneous branches are seen to run
forwards to the anterior part of the perinæum, and communiBranch cate with the superficial perineal artery. A vein accompanies the
