Pudic nerve is
The pudic vein has the same connections, and the same branches
as the artery, with the exception that the dorsal vein of the penis
does not join it.
The pudic nerve is derived from the sacral plexus, and
with ar- distributes offsets corresponding to the branches of the pudic tery artery. The nerve enters the posterior part of the ischiolike it on
rectal fossa, and supplies there the inferior hæmorrhoidal
and ends (p. 398. ) and a large perineal branch. Much diminished
penis. in size, it continues with the artery without branching,
pierces the triangular ligament of the urethra, and is continued onward to the dorsum of the penis with the dorsal
branch of the pudic artery. Its termination is described
at page 419.
