triangular ligament, the vessel extends forwards on the dorsum of a branch
the penis as far as the corona glandis, where it ends in many
branches which enter that structure. In this course the artery
supplies the integuments and the body of the penis. This artery Pecumay be a separate branch of the internal iliac, and arrive at its
destination by a course along the side of the prostate, and through
the triangular ligament of the urethra.
