Dissec- Dissection. Divide the transversalis fascia by a longitudinal
incision begun a little above the abdominal ring, and continued
downwards through that spot, so as to trace a prolongation ofthe
fascia on the cord. With the handle of the scalpel the fascia may
be easily reflected to each side from the subperitoneal fat. After the
subperitoneal fat has been seen, let it be removed to trace the
