Dissection.-Cut across the cord near the abdominal ring, and Dissecturn it upwards on the abdomen. Below Poupart's ligament will deep
be sometimes seen a thin band (deep crural arch) passing inwards
to the os pubis. The dissector should define this band with care.
Afterwards the remaining vessels of the abdominal wall should be and of
exposed, viz. the epigastric and circumflex iliac, and the ending of vessels .
the internal mammary artery. On turning up the outer edge of
