Seat of stricture. —The stricture on the intestine is generally found at the margin of the tendinous opening in the
abdominal wall ; and it should be remembered that this
opening is at the upper part, not in the centre of the swelling. The constriction may be removed by cutting upwards,
but there is not any vessel to be avoided in the operation.
