femoral, tumour. For instance, there may be femoral hernia below
Poupart's ligament, with the femoral vessels ; obturator
hernia through the obturator foramen, with the artery of the ischia- same name ; and ischiadic hernia through the ischiadic notch.
The femoral hernia, as the most important, will be noticed
presently ; but the student must refer to some special treatise
for his information respecting the other abdominal herniæ.
