Serous covering of the duodenum. The first part of the Perito
duodenum is surrounded by peritoneum, like the stomach ; the duodenext part of the intestine is covered only in front ; and the
last part, that crosses the aorta, is but slightly in contact
with the serous membrane, for at first it lies between the
layers of the transverse meso- colon, and then beneath the
upper part of the superior mesenteric artery.
