Lastly, it leaves the abdomen by an aperture in the tendinous part of the diaphragm, on the right of the aortic
opening. The vena cava is joined by some branches from Branchthe abdominal viscera, and by others corresponding to the
branches of the aorta that are supplied to the parietes of
