from the left semilunar ganglion, and by an offset from the right
pneumogastric nerve.
c. The hepatic plexus is continued on the vena portæ, the hepatic
artery, and the bile duct to the transverse fissure of the liver,
where it enters the liver and ramifies on the vessels. Whilst
ascending in the small omentum the plexus is joined on the left
side by offsets from the left vagus and phrenic nerves.-(Swan.)
