SECTION IV.
ANATOMY OF THE VISCERA OF THE ABDOMEN.
THE STOMACH.
tion .
Defini- THE stomach is a dilated pouch between the oesophagus and
the small intestine, into which the food is received to be
changed into chyme.
Separate and blow up the
Dissection. ― - To see the form of the stomach, detach the spleen
and cut through the duodenum near the pylorus. Then blow up
stomach. the stomach moderately and clean the surface.
Form,
