Borders. The upper border, or small curve of the Upper
stomach, is concave towards the left opening, but convex at
the opposite end ; and the lower border, or large curve, is lower
convex, except near the right end, where it is concave.
The concavity of the one border corresponds to the con- differvexity of the other. An arterial arch and a fold of peri- outline.
