3. Fibrous or submucous coat. -By removing the muscoat is cular layer over a small spot, the cellular or fibrous coat will
firm . appear as a white shining stratum. Formed of fine areolar
tissue, this coat gives strength to the stomach, and serves as
a bed in which the vessels and nerves ramify before their
final distribution to the mucous coat. If a small opening is
made in this membrane, the mucous coat projects through it
when the stomach is distended with air.
