Serous coat
STRUCTURE. —In the small intestine the wall is formed
by the same number of layers as in the stomach, viz. serous,
muscular, cellular, and mucous ; and these have the same
position from within outwards. These different structures
are to be examined on the duodenum, and on pieces taken
from the upper part of the jejunum, from the lower end of
the ileum, and from the middle of the small intestine.
pieces of intestine, when obtained, are to be distended
with air.
