muscular layer. To the greater part of the small intestine
(jejunum and ileum) it furnishes an entire covering, except
like that at the posterior aspect, where the vessels enter. At that
stomach, spot a space exists, resembling those at the borders of the
stomach, where the peritoneum is reflected off to form the
except mesentery. The peritoneum surrounds the duodenum only
duode- partly ; this peculiarity has been described at p. 457.
