The solitary follicles are found all through the large inmost in testine, scattered here and there ; but they are in greatest
number in the cæcum, and in the vermiform appendix. They
are whitish rounded bodies from to a line in diameter,
and are situate in the submucous cellular layer amongst the
tubules. These follicular glands are simple sacs with a dilated
cavity and a narrow neck opening into the intestine, being
in form something like a small rounded fruit with a stalk.
and form.
