STRUCTURE OF THE LIVER. -Two coats envelop the liver,
structure viz. a serous and a cellular. The substance of the liver
cased by consists of a collection of small secreting bodies, called
lobules or acini ; together with a large proportion of vessels,
which are concerned both in the production of its secretion
and in the nutrition of the organ.
