The URETER is the tube by which the fluid secreted in the Ureter ;
kidney is conveyed to the bladder. Its anatomy must be
studied when the body is in a suitable position. Between length.
its origin and termination this duct measures from sixteen to
eighteen inches in length. Its size corresponds commonly to size
that of a large quill, but near the kidney it is dilated into a
funnel-shaped part, named pelvis, and near the bladder it is
again somewhat dilated, though its aperture of termination is
the narrowest part of the tube.
varies.
