beneath the peritoneum, and is directed obliquely downwards
and inwards along the posterior wall of the abdomen as far
as the pelvis, where it becomes almost horizontal in direction
in the posterior false ligament of the bladder. At first the and conureter is placed over the psoas muscle, inclining on the right
side towards the inferior vena cava, and then on the common
