From the disposition and appearance of the seminal tubes, Tubes
the several parts of the testis take their name. Thus, where their
they are collected into separate masses, they form the lobes
of the testis ; as they enter the mediastinum testis they are
named vasa recta ; where they communicate in the mediastinum they produce the rete testis ; and, lastly, as they leave
the upper part of the gland, and become convoluted, they
are called coni vasculosi.
