three lumbar vertebræ, to their intervertebral substance,
and to the fibro- cartilage between the third and fourth vertebræ. The left pillar, which is situate more on the side of
the spine, is partly concealed by the aorta, and does not reach
so far as the right by the depth of a vertebra or of an intervertebral substance. In each pillar the fleshy fibres that Arrange
