SPINAL LUMBAR NERVES. ― The anterior divisions of the
lumbar nerves, except the last, enter into the lumbar plexus.
Five in number, they increase in size from the first to the
last, and are joined by filaments of the sympathetic near the
intervertebral foramina. They supply branches also to the
muscles ; psoas and quadratus lumborum muscles.
