aries.
The cavity of the pelvis is but a part of the general space Definiof the abdomen. It is situate below the brim or inlet of the the
true pelvis, and is bounded behind by the sacrum and coccyx, here
and, laterally and in front, by the innominate bones. In- with its
feriorly, or towards the perinæum, the floor of the cavity is tion
formed by the fascia reflected from the wall to the viscera, boundand by some muscles that will be afterwards seen. In the
interior are contained the urinary bladder, the lower end of Conthe rectum, and some of the generative organs, according to
the sex. All these parts have vessels, nerves, and lymphatics
connected with them, and the serous membrane is reflected
over them.
tents.
