Differ- ent terms
It may here be remarked that the term " pelvic" is not applied
always, as in the previous description, to the fascia in its whole
applied extent from the brim to the outlet of the pelvis, but that the name
" obturator" is given to the part of it below the recto- vesical
piece. Those who make this distinction describe the pelvic fascia
to the fascia.
