The URETHRA is the excretory passage for the urine and urethra ; semen, and reaches from the bladder to the end of the penis.
length ; Its length varies from seven and a half to nine inches and a
half, and it presents one or two curves according to the state
it is of the penis. At first the canal is directed forwards through
accord the triangular ligament of the perinæum, and next upwards
the con- to the body ofthe penis, forming a large curve with the concavity to the pubes. Thence to its termination the urethra
