SECTION IV.
VESSELS AND NERVES OF THE PELVIS.
THIS section is to be used by the dissectors of both the male
and female pelvis.
and In the pelvis are the internal iliac vessels and their vessels
branches to the viscera ; the sacral nerves and the sacral nerves
plexus ; and the sympathetic nerve, consisting both of a pelvis .
