The mucous membrane has the same general structure as
in the colon, but towards the anus the secretory apparatus
gradually disappears.
Blood- vessels. -The arteries are supplied from three different
sources they are, superior hæmorrhoidal, from the inferior mesenteric ; middle hæmorrhoidal, from the internal iliac artery ; and
Veins inferior hæmorrhoidal, from the internal pudic. The veins are
deficient in valves, and communicate freely around the lower end
of the gut. Above, they join the inferior mesenteric vein, and,
through it, reach the vena portæ ; and, posteriorly, they pour
some blood into the internal iliac vein by branches corresponding
to the middle hæmorrhoidal artery.
