SECTION VI.
ANATOMY OF THE VISCERA OF THE FEMALE.
in the pelvis.
Viscera THE viscera of the female pelvis consist of those common to
the male and female, viz. the bladder and urethra, with the
rectum ; and of those that are special to the female, viz. the
organs of generation.
