SUPERFICIAL FASCIA. 599
To raise the skin from this part an incision of about four inches in
length is to be made from the spine of the pubes along the inner
border of the thigh : from its lower end another cut is to be directed
outwards across the front of the limb to the outer aspect ; and
from its upper end the knife is to be carried along the line of
Poupart's ligament as far as the crest of the innominate bone.
The piece of skin included by the lines above stated is to be raised
and turned outwards, without taking with it the subcutaneous fat
