The fascia lata is the special deep aponeurosis of the Fascia
thigh which surrounds the limb, giving it a firm sheath, and sursends inwards septa between the different muscles. This limb;
membranous investment is of a bluish white colour, and of
very variable thickness, though it is always stronger on the strength
outer than on the inner aspect of the limb, in consequence
of the insertion into it of the gluteus maximus and tensor
vaginæ femoris muscles. In fat bodies it is sometimes so
slight as to be taken away with the superficial fascia.
varies.
