of the partition is now visible, but its characters are ascertained in the dissection of the abdomen (p. 444.).
After having learnt the anatomy of the parts in the thigh
amongst which a femoral hernia lies, the student is prepared
to understand the course this takes, the coverings it receives,
and the seat of its stricture.
