The TENSOR VAGINÆ FEMORIS is the smallest and the
femoris most external of the outer set of muscles. It takes origin
from the front of the crest of the ilium, at its outer aspect,
and from the superior of the two spinous processes of the
same bone, and is inserted into the fascia lata about three
inches below the great trochanter of the femur. At its
origin the muscle is situate between the sartorius and gluteus
medius, and its fibres are blended with the latter. Beneath
it are the ascending branches of the external circumflex
artery, and a branch of the superior gluteal nerve that enters
it at the under aspect. A strong sheath of fascia surrounds
the muscle.
