- Dissection. — The common tendon of the vasti and rectus, with
the com- the expansion from it over the knee-joint, can be demonstrated
tendon by means of an incision along the middle of the patella to the head
of the tibia. This cut will allow the thin expansion to be reflected inwards and outwards, so as to lay bare the tendon. A
strong transverse band will be likewise seen on each side of the
patella ; the outer of the two is the strongest.
