The POPLITEAL SPACE, or the ham, is a hollow behind the The
knee-joint, which contains the large vessels of the limb,
and allows of the free flexion of the joint. When dissected, situathis interval, which has the form of a lozenge, extends up- extent.
wards for one-third of the femur, and downwards for onesixth of the tibia ; but in the natural condition of the parts
the sides are approximated by the fascia of the limb, and the
space is limited almost to the region of the joint.
ries ;
The ham is situate between the attachments of the muscles Boundato the condyles of the femur, and the lateral boundaries are
therefore formed in part by the muscles of the thigh (hamstrings), and in part by those of the leg. Thus, on the
