The special or deep fascia on the posterior aspect of the Deep
leg covers the muscles, and sends a thick process between
the deep and superficial layers. Above it is continuous with Contithe investing membrane of the thigh, and receives offsets
from the tendons about the knee ; below it joins the internal
annular ligament. Externally it is continued uninterruptedly and
from one aspect of the limb to another, but internally it is
fixed tothe edge of the tibia. Veins are transmitted through
it from the superficial to the deep vessels.
