The POSTERIOR TIBIAL ARTERY is one of the branches resulting from the bifurcation of the popliteal trunk. The
trunk of the vessel extends from the lower border of the po- Extent.
pliteus muscle to the lower part of the internal annular
ligament, where it enters the sole of the foot, and ends in
two plantar branches. At its origin the artery lies midway Course.
between the tibia and fibula, but as it approaches the lower
part of the leg it gradually inclines inwards, and at its termination is placed below the tibia, in the centre of the hollow
between the heel and inner ankle.
