veins.
The posterior tibial veins begin on the inner side of the Posfoot by the union of the plantar veins ; they ascend one on tibial
each side of their artery, and unite with the anterior tibial
veins at the lower border of the popliteus to form the large
popliteal vein. They receive the peroneal veins, and branches
corresponding to the offsets of the artery : further, branches
connect them with the saphenous veins.
