Plantar fascia. The special fascia of the sole of the Plantar
foot is of a pearly white colour and great strength, and sends
septa between the muscles. Its thickness varies in different
parts of the foot, and from this circumstance, and from the
existence of longitudinal hollows where the two chief inter-
