The lateral parts of the fascia are thinner than the central one. On the inner margin of the foot the fascia has
but little strength, and is continued to the dorsum ; but on
the outer side it is increased in thickness, and presents a
strong band between the os calcis and the projection of the
fifth metatarsal bone.
