The transverse metatarsal ligament is a strong fibrous Transband that connects together the anterior extremities of all metathe metatarsal bones, and resembles a similar structure in ligament
the hand. To its hinder part is connected a thin fascia that
covers the interossei muscles. It is concealed by the transversalis pedis, and by the tendons, vessels, and nerves of the
toes.
