CUTANEOUS NERVES. All the superficial nerves on the
cutane- front of the leg and foot are derived from branches of the
popliteal trunks, viz., from the musculo-cutaneous and anterior tibial nerves of the external popliteal, and from the
external saphenous nerve of the internal popliteal. Some
inconsiderable offsets to the sides of the leg from the internal
and external saphenous do not require separate notice.
