certain toes ;
The musculo-cutaneous nerve has a cutaneous termination, and
its destination is to the dorsum of the foot and toes . Perforating
supplies the fascia in the lower third of the leg, it divides into two principal
branches (inner and outer) , which give digital nerves to the sides
of all the toes, except the outer part of the little toe, and the condivides tiguous sides of the great toe and the next. The digital branches
may be traced in the integument as far as the end of the last
phalanx.
