Peculiarities in the vessels. The anterior tibial may be small, or even
anterior wanting, in which case the place of its diminished or deficient part will
be supplied by the posterior tibial or the peroneal artery. On the dorsum
of the foot it is often removed farther outwards than the direction of a
line from the centre of the ankle to the posterior part of the first interand dor- osseous space. The place of the dorsal artery of the foot may be taken sal ar- tery.
