Dissection. In the dissection ofthe ligaments ofthe articulations, Dissecit is necessary to detach the muscles and tendons from the particular
joint, and to remove the cellular or fibrous structure that may obscure or conceal the ligamentous bands. In the knee-joint a kind of a capcapsule is to be defined around the articular surfaces of the bones ; and the
and there are four other ligaments, anterior and posterior, internal ligaand external, which will be found as thickened bands at their
