VITREOUS BODY. - A transparent mass fills the greater Vitreous
part of the space within the coats of the eyeball, which has
been named vitreous body from its resemblance to glass ; it
consists of a clear aqueous fluid, contained in a translucent
membrane, and has the consistence of jelly.
