Canal of Petit.— Around the margin of the lens is a
small canal, about two lines across, which has received the
above name. It is placed beneath the plaited part of the
hyaloid membrane, and is excavated in the substance of the
anterior vitreous body. When the canal has been opened and disculated. tended with air, it is sacculated at regular intervals, like the
large intestine, in consequence of the inflation of the plaits
of the hyaloid membrane.
