The lens is contained in a capsule, and is seated in a situahollow on the front of the vitreous body. The anterior part connec
projects towards the iris and the pupil ; whilst the posterior
is received in the vitreous body, and is attached thereto by
fibrous processes that are fixed to the capsule. The circumference is below the level of the surface of the vitreous mass,
and corresponds to the canal of Petit.
