Changes in situa- tion ;
form ,
-- Changes with age. In infancy the lens is situate further
forwards than in adult age, and touches the iris. Its form
is nearly spherical in the fetus, but its convexity decreases
with age, particularly on the anterior aspect, until the lens
colour, becomes flattened in old people. In the fetus it is reddish
in colour, is soft, and is not quite transparent ; in youth and
consist- mature age it is firm and clear, and in old age it becomes
denser and of a yellowish colour.
