Fibro- serous mem- brane
Lining membrane ofthe osseous labyrinth. -A thin membrane of a fibro- serous character lines the vestibule, the semilines the circular canals, and the scale of the cochlea, and is likewise laby- rinth ; continued into the aqueducts of the vestibule and cochlea.*
On the outer wall of the vestibule it closes the openings into the
tympanic cavity. The outer surface of the membrane is
adherent to the bone ; but the inner is covered by an epilium and thelium, and secretes a thin serous fluid, liquor Cotunnii, or
This fluid in the interior fills the scale of the
