form ;
The utricle, or the common sinus, is the larger of the two The
sacs, and is situate at the posterior and upper part of the situation
vestibule, corresponding to the fovea semi-elliptica in the
roof. It is transversely oval in form, and connected with it and
posteriorly are three looped tubes that are prolonged into the
semicircular canals. The sac and its prolongations are filled contains
with a clear fluid, like water, which is named endolymph ;
and in its wall is a small calcareous deposit (otolith) opposite and
the entrance of the nerve into it.
